oc:kn_02d573b6 a oc:AntiPattern,
        oc:KnowledgeNode ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When creating product usage report or summary emails" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Never send empty or irrelevant usage reports. Personalization must reflect actual usage — empty reports are worse than no report." ;
    oc:hasRationale "Empty reports signal that the product isn't providing value, accelerating churn rather than preventing it." ;
    oc:severityLevel "HIGH" .

oc:kn_0ceae8c7 a oc:DesignPrinciple,
        oc:KnowledgeNode ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When creating win-back sequences for churned customers" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Win-back emails for cancelled customers should have no guilt or desperation tone, focus on genuine updates and improvements, personalize based on known cancellation reason, and make return easy." ;
    oc:hasRationale "Customers are more likely to return if their original cancellation reason has been addressed; guilt-tripping permanently damages the relationship." ;
    oc:severityLevel "HIGH" .

oc:kn_32ae9d60 a oc:KnowledgeNode,
        oc:WorkflowStrategy ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When processing NPS survey responses" ;
    oc:directiveContent "NPS follow-up must differ by score segment: Promoters (9-10) get thanked and asked for review/referral; Passives (7-8) get asked what would make it a 10; Detractors (0-6) get personal outreach to understand issues." ;
    oc:hasRationale "A single follow-up approach wastes promoters (best source of growth) and fails to recover detractors (highest churn risk)." ;
    oc:severityLevel "HIGH" .

oc:kn_4a8c77b5 a oc:Heuristic,
        oc:KnowledgeNode ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When creating onboarding sequences for users who just converted to paid" ;
    oc:directiveContent "New customer series differs from new user series: customers have committed financially, so focus on reinforcement and expansion rather than conversion." ;
    oc:hasRationale "Treating new customers like prospects misses the opportunity to reinforce their purchase decision and deepen engagement." ;
    oc:severityLevel "MEDIUM" .

oc:kn_5e2b1270 a oc:KnowledgeNode,
        oc:Standard ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When communicating price increases" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Pricing update emails must announce 30-60 days before change, be clear and transparent about the why, grandfather existing customers if possible, and give options (annual lock-in, downgrade)." ;
    oc:hasRationale "Honesty and advance notice build trust even during price increases; surprise charges destroy customer relationships." ;
    oc:severityLevel "CRITICAL" .

oc:kn_6702f3ef a oc:DesignPrinciple,
        oc:KnowledgeNode ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When designing any lifecycle or campaign email" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Every email type must have a clearly defined trigger, a single primary goal, and a defined format (single email or sequence). Never create emails without explicit trigger conditions." ;
    oc:hasRationale "Undefined triggers lead to irrelevant sends; unclear goals dilute impact; wrong format wastes touchpoints." ;
    oc:severityLevel "HIGH" .

oc:kn_7457a65f a oc:Heuristic,
        oc:KnowledgeNode ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When designing win-back sequences for expired trials" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Segment expired trial win-back by engagement level: high-engagement users get friction-removal to convert; low-engagement users get a fresh start with more onboarding; no-engagement users get asked what happened and offered a demo." ;
    oc:hasRationale "A one-size-fits-all approach fails because the barrier to conversion differs drastically based on how much they used the product." ;
    oc:severityLevel "MEDIUM" .

oc:kn_d8146604 a oc:Constraint,
        oc:KnowledgeNode ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When timing review request emails" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Ask-for-review emails must NOT be sent after billing issues or bugs. Best timing is after positive support interactions, measurable achievements, or renewals." ;
    oc:hasRationale "Asking for a review after a negative experience generates poor reviews or no response, and can damage the relationship further." ;
    oc:severityLevel "CRITICAL" .

oc:kn_eeb48f0d a oc:KnowledgeNode,
        oc:Standard ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When building dunning/payment recovery email sequences" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Failed payment recovery should assume the failure is accidental, use clear and direct language without guilt, provide a single CTA to update payment, and escalate urgency across 3-4 emails over 7-14 days." ;
    oc:hasRationale "Accusing customers of intentional non-payment destroys trust; escalating urgency with clarity maximizes recovery rates." ;
    oc:severityLevel "HIGH" .

oc:kn_f56474af a oc:Heuristic,
        oc:KnowledgeNode ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When reaching out to users showing signs of struggle" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Proactive support emails should use genuine concern tone, reference specific observed behavior if data allows, come from a real person (support/CSM), and contain no sales pitch." ;
    oc:hasRationale "Users who receive helpful, non-salesy outreach during struggle moments become more loyal than users who never struggled at all." ;
    oc:severityLevel "MEDIUM" .

